06-07 May - Panettone (Christmas Bread)

Sponge
- 1/4 cup warm water
- 1 teaspoon dry yeast
- 1/2 cup flour

Mix sponge well, no lumps, cover and let rise 6 hours or overnight. 

Marinate raisins with grappa for 6 hours.
- 2/3 cup raisins
- grappa

In a large bowl, add together
- 2 whole eggs and 4 egg yolks
- 5 tablespoon butter
- 3/4 cup sugar
- 1 tablespoon vanilla
- 1/4 cup water
- marinade grappa fluid (put aside the raisins)

Mixins 
- 1/2 cup candied citrons
- marinated raisins
- orange rind
- lemon rind


Whisk altogether until very mixed. Add sponge to egg mixture then add 
- 4-4 1/2 cup flour 
until you get a soft but workable dough. 
Flour board and knead dough until soft and elastic. Grease a bowl and let rise covered with plastic wrap for 6 hours. Flatten your dough and add raisins, 1/2 cup candided citron, rind of 1 orange and 1 lemon. Add flour to fruit to keep from lumping. Work fruit into dough. Grease a mold (flour pot - coffee can) with melted butter then flour. Add your bread dough and let rise to 2/3 of your mold. Bake in a preheated oven at 
400F for 5 minutes
375 for 10 minutes
350 until browned. 
Run knive around bread in mold and remove.